text: The western long-legged bush frog (Philautus kakipanjang) is a frog. It lives in Malaysia. People have seen it 750 meters above sea level in Kubah National Park. This frog lives in western Sarawak. Scientists found it in forests on mountains, in two national parks. It has a long nose, long legs, and a large amount of webbed skin on its feet. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Philautus kakipanjang
